      • setTag

        @NonNull
public ThingIFAPI.Builder setTag(@Nullable
                                          java.lang.String tag)
        Set tag to this ThingIFAPI instance. tag is used to distinguish storage area of instance.
        If the api instance is tagged with same string, It will be overwritten.
        If the api instance is tagged with different string, Different key is used to store the instance.

        Please refer to ThingIFAPI.loadFromStoredInstance(Context, String) as well.
        Parameters:
        tag - if null or empty string is passed, it will be ignored.
        Returns:
        builder instance for chaining call.

      • _newBuilder

        @NonNull
public static ThingIFAPI.Builder _newBuilder(@NonNull
                                                      KiiApp app,
                                                      @NonNull
                                                      Owner owner,
                                                      @NonNull
                                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Class<? extends Action>> actionTypes,
                                                      @NonNull
                                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Class<? extends TargetState>> stateTypes)
        Instantiate new Builder without Context. This method is for internal use only. Do not call it from your application.
        Parameters:
        app - Kii Cloud Application.
        owner - Specify who uses the ThingIFAPI.
        actionTypes - the format of key of actionTypes is "[alias]:[actionName]". i.e. if you register an action class, the alias name is AirConditionerAlias and the action name is turnPower, then the key should be "AirConditionerAlias:turnPower".
        stateTypes - the key of stateTypes is alias name.
        Returns:
        Builder instance.

      • registerAction

        @NonNull
public ThingIFAPI.Builder registerAction(@NonNull
                                                  java.lang.String alias,
                                                  @NonNull
                                                  java.lang.String actionName,
                                                  @NonNull
                                                  java.lang.Class<? extends Action> actionClass)
        Register list of Action subclasses to specified alias. The registered action classes will be used for serialization/deserialization the action. If the same alias already registered, then will be updated
        Parameters:
        alias - Alias to register
        actionName - Name of action
        actionClass - List of Action subclasses
        Returns:
        builder instance for chaining call.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - This exception is thrown if one or more following conditions are met.
        • actionClass is non static inner class
        • actionClass has more than one field/s
        • getActionName() method returns null or empty string

      • registerTargetState

        Parameters:

        stateClass - Class of TargetState subclass.
        Returns:
